 contrast report an accessibility issue  log in profile logout subscribe now haaretz  israel news thursday july   av   time in israel  am search click to search log in profile ehud barak ehud barak israel’s th prime minister was born the eldest of four brothers on kibbutz mishmar hasharon on february   in  at the age of  he enlisted in the idf and accepted into israel’s most elite commando unit sayeret matkal he would later go on to command the unit as a soldier the young barak quickly distinguished himself for his ingenuity bravery and coolness under fire he participated in a number of publicized commando operations most notably when he led a raid inside beirut disguised as a woman barak also helped plan the hostage rescue operation at entebbe uganda in  and led the hostage rescue attempt on a hijacked sabena airliner while disguised as a plane mechanic in the yom kippur war of  barak commanded a tank regiment which among other things helped rescue a beleaguered paratrooper battalion suffering heavy losses in the chinese farm in the sinai desert barak went on to serve as head of military intelligence and was later appointed by then prime minister yitzhak rabin as the chief of general staff of the israel defense forces he retired from military life in  after  years of service by which time he had become israel’s most decorated soldier during his time in the army barak earned a ba in physics and mathematics from the hebrew university in jerusalem and then a ma in economic engineering systems from stanford university immediately following his military service barak joined the labor party as a politician barak served as minister of the interior and then as minister of foreign affairs when shimon peres replaced the slain yitzhak rabin as prime minister he was elected to the knesset in  where he served as a member of the knesset foreign affairs and defense committee in  after peres lost the premiership to benjamin netanyahu barak became the leader of the labor party in  barak defeated netanyahu in national elections becoming israel’s th prime minister his most significant act as prime minister was to order the withdrawal of all idf troops from southern lebanon effectively ending israel’s controversial year presence there the move was heralded by many as a brave and longoverdue decision while others harshly criticized it for its perceived security threat and for the manner of its overnight execution barak also attempted and failed to reach a peace agreement with syria at the camp david summit in  mediated by thenus president bill clinton barak met with plo leader yasser arafat the talks failed and shortly afterwards the second intifada broke out unleashing an unprecedented wave of terror attacks against israelis in  against the backdrop of failed peace negotiations and escalating palestinian violence barak was soundly defeated by ariel sharon of the likud in elections for prime minister which barak himself had called after several years in the private sector barak returned to politics in  but dropped out of the race to lead the labor party after polls showed he was unpopular with voters in  he made yet another attempt to regain control of the labor party and succeeded in june of that year shortly thereafter he was sworn in as minister of defense by thenprime minister ehud olmert as defense minister barak oversaw operation cast lead a threeweek idf campaign inside the gaza strip launched in the wake of ongoing rocket fire from the coastal territory at civilian targets inside southern israel the operation was viewed by most israelis as a wellexecuted and necessary military act of defense but came under international criticism for what was seen as excessive and disproportionate use of force inside the densely populated gaza strip in the  elections the barakled labor party won only  out of  knesset seats relegating israels once strongest party to the fourth largest much of the blame for the historic loss of mandates was directed at barak who continued to disappoint many labor purists by agreeing to keep the party in a likudled government in exchange for the defense portfolio opinion ehud run away barak has been the biggest disappointment of the israeli left the hopes pinned on him continue to explode in the faces of the masses that comprise this wounded camp by carolina landsmann  this is a primium article  comments  explained meet the two men who want to lead israel’s labor party back to power amir peretz has already led the party but has jumped ship twice while avi gabbay has built up a résumé as a bigtime ceo by allison kaplan sommer  this is a primium article israeli spring ehud barak says time is ripe for broad front to topple netanyahu government barak warning against netanyahu governments drift to apartheid says signs on the ground point to an impending israeli spring by gili cohen   comments  opinion beware the third coming of ehud barak the belief that ehud barak is the one man who can defeat the right and if reelected prime minister will lead israel into an era of peace is wrong on every level by haim ramon  this is a primium article ehud barak warns israel faces slippery slope toward apartheid if israel keeps controlling palestinians inevitable result will be either nonjewish or nondemocratic state former israeli pm tells conflict zones tim sebastian in deutsche welle tv interview by allison kaplan sommer  this article contains a video  comments  opinion generous with state secrets if revealing classified information endangers security as the israeli defense establishment claims then netanyahu is a walking – or rather a convoytraveling – security risk by amir oren  this is a primium article opinion ehud barak didnt flee while it is easy to criticize the former prime minister we should never forget his decision to withdraw israeli troops from lebanon by uri misgav  this is a primium article  comments  opinion barak is more dangerous than bibi despite what some disillusioned flatterers are saying ehud barak isn’t the man to fight the good fight against netanyahu’s rotten rightwing regime by haim baram  this is a primium article  comments  opinion ehud barak is israel’s only chance today’s barak understands what prime minister barak didn’t want to know nurturing the settlements leads to nothing but devastation he’s capable of beating the ultranationalist right in a way shimon peres never could by zeev sternhell  this is a primium article  comments  in response why ehud baraks responsible left argument wont convince israelis micah goodman responds to ehud baraks review of his book catch someone who aspires to lead the public should know where the public stands by micah goodman  this is a primium article  comments  load articles loading trending now these four things will get you barred from entering israel under its new bds travel ban did adelson just dump netanyahu this unprecedented front page speaks volumes jordan mad at israels portrayal of embassy crisis and absurd heros welcome by netanyahu exclusive behind the scenes of us efforts to defuse israels crisis with jordan skip  break when jewish parents decide not to circumcise why jews from libya are worried about the fate of the country’s jewish artifacts when israel threatens palestinians with a new nakba it threatens itself with extinction after being barred from flight bds activists claim israel gave airlines a blacklist what the gifts jared kushner received from the russians tell us about moscow how smart are the new smart cameras israel wants to install near the temple mount skip  ruler support close skip  pop under skip  skip  skip  skip  yoyo code hdc site skip  crazy egg skip  collecting surfing data  responsive skip  skip  skip  skip  access list by ip script skip  skip  skip  skip  skip  yoyo code hdc site skip  crazy egg skip  collecting surfing data  responsive skip  skip  skip  skip  skip  skip  access list by ip script skip  skip  barak ehud  worldcat identities barak ehud  overview 